warning[W10007]: issue with attribute value
  ┌─ tests/move_check/warning_suppression/expect_category_unused.move:4:14
  │
4 │     #[expect(unused)]
  │              ^^^^^^ 'unused' matches multiple diagnostics, but 'expect' may only be used for individual diagnostics
  │
  = Use '#[allow(unused)]' instead

warning[W09002]: unused variable
  ┌─ tests/move_check/warning_suppression/expect_category_unused.move:6:13
  │
6 │         let x = 0u64;
  │             ^ Unused local variable 'x'. Consider removing or prefixing with an underscore: '_x'
  │
  = This warning can be suppressed with '#[allow(unused_variable)]' applied to the 'module' or module member ('const', 'fun', or 'struct')
